Even though an experimental vaccine appears to be able to reduce the mortality rate of Ebola, no cure has yet been sufficiently effective to treat the existing infection.
Although administration of a cocktail of antibodies, ZMapp, initially showed promising signs in the field, formal studies have demonstrated that its ability to limit deaths did not meet expectations.
In the PALM trial, the ZMapp served as a de témoin, meaning that the scientists used it as a reference and compared the three other treatments.
The American Gymnastics Federation supports the letter of the United States Olympic Committee and accepts the absolute necessity of the Olympic family to promote a safe environment for all our athletes.
We agree with the USOC's statement that the interests of our athletes and clubs, and their sport, could be better served by moving forward and making significant changes within our organisation rather than revoking accreditation.
USA Gymnastics supports an independent investigation that could shed light on the way in which the abuse of proportion so courageously described by the survivors of Larry Nassar could go unnoticed for so long and adopt any change necessary and appropriate.
USA Gymnastics and the USOC have the same objective: to make gymnastics, as well as other sports, as safe as possible so that athletes can pursue their dreams in a safe, positive and responsible environment.
Throughout the 1960s, Brzezinski worked for John F. Kennedy as a counselor, then for the administration of Lyndon B. Johnson.
During the 1976 elections, he was Carter's foreign policy adviser, then was National Security Adviser (NSA) from 1977 to 1981, succeeding Henry Kissinger.
During his time at the NSA, he helped Carter to resolve diplomatically international issues such as the Camp David Accords in 1978, the normalization of relations between the United States and China in the late 1970s, the Iranian Revolution and its aftermath such as the 1979 hostage crisis in Iran, and the 1979 invasion of Soviet forces in Afghanistan.
