The 802.11n standard operates on both the 2.4 GHz and 5.0 GHz frequencies.
This will allow backward compatibility with the 802.11a, b and g iterations, provided that the station has two radios.
The Wi-Fi 802.11n standard is significantly faster than its predecessors, with a theoretical maximum speed of 600 Mbit/s.
